-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Air Canada, Hudson's Bay, Eldorado Gold 
-- 
-- Fri Apr 04, 2014 05:54AM EDT
-- None



April 4 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Air Canada and Hudson's Bay, on Friday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Air Canada <ACb.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$10.50 from C$10.25 * Hudson's Bay Co <HBC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity, Credit Suisse cuts target price  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Friday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Aecon Group Inc <ARE.TO>: RBC starts with outperform; price target C$23 * Air Canada <ACb.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$10.50 from C$10.25; rating buy * Eldorado Gold Corp <ELD.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy rating  * Eldorado Gold Corp <ELD.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts target price to C$8.50 from C$9 * Hudson's Bay Co <HBC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts target to C$21.50 from C$22.50; buy * Hudson's Bay Co <HBC.TO>: Credit Suisse cuts target to C$18 from C$19; rating neutral * Melcor REIT <MR_u.TO>: NBF starts with sector perform rating; target price of C$11.50 * Newalta Corp <NAL.TO>: National Bank Financial ups target to C$23.50 from C$21; outperform * Richelieu Hardware Ltd <RCH.TO>: NBF raises target price to C$54 from C$51; outperform * Veresen Inc <VSN.TO>: National Bank Financial resumes coverage with sector perform rating